<p>I have this attribute in a class, that is also an object. For some reason, whenever I try to use a constructor for it, it gives me a Null Pointer Exception.</p>  <p>This is the Class of the Object:</p>  <pre><code>    public class Posicion {     private int filas;     private int columnas;      public void Posicion(int x, int y)     {         filas = x;         columnas = y;     } } </code></pre>  <p>This is the class that has the object as an attribute:</p>  <pre><code>public class Casillas {     protected char simbolo;     protected Posicion coordenadas;      public void Casillas(char simbolo, Posicion coordenadas)      {         this.simbolo = simbolo;         this.coordenadas = coordenadas;     } } </code></pre>  <p>and this is where I get the Null Pointer Exception (first line of the "inicio" method):</p>  <pre><code>public class R2D2 extends Casillas {     public R2D2 inicio(int x, int y)     {         coordenadas.Posicion(x, y);          R2D2 art = new R2D2();         art.Casillas('A', coordenadas);          return art;     } } </code></pre>  <p>I appreciate all the feedback I can get.</p>  <p>EDIT: This is java language.</p>